{"actor":"Aaron Lippold","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-03T20:00:26Z","event_type":"claimed","id":75,"issue_id":"gh-action-security-audit-vek","new_value":"{\"assignee\":\"Aaron Lippold\",\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"gh-action-security-audit-vek\",\"title\":\"Fix base64 -d portability — fails silently on stock macOS\",\"description\":\"Line 217: base64 -d is GNU coreutils flag. Stock macOS uses -D. The 2\\u003e/dev/null || true masks the failure, so all workflow files end up empty on macOS. Detect the correct flag at script startup. This is the highest priority fix.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T23:55:20Z\",\"created_by\":\"alippold\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T23:55:20Z\"}"}
