{"actor":"Aaron Lippold","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-03T20:08:53Z","event_type":"claimed","id":77,"issue_id":"gh-action-security-audit-di0","new_value":"{\"assignee\":\"Aaron Lippold\",\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"gh-action-security-audit-di0\",\"title\":\"Add trap EXIT for temp file cleanup\",\"description\":\"Lines 237, 385, 369: Script creates temp files via mktemp but has no trap handler. If killed (Ctrl-C, SIGTERM, set -e failure), files are orphaned in /tmp. Add: trap cleanup EXIT with a function that removes TABLE_ROWS, TABLE_ROWS.csv, ORG_SECRETS_FILE, and optionally AUDIT_DIR.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T23:55:20Z\",\"created_by\":\"alippold\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T23:55:20Z\"}"}
